<subSubSection id="C363AAB6FF9CC514FF12F9FBFAA4FE83" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BC6F93DFF9CC514FF12F9FBFAA4FE83" blockId="16.[151,1436,1919,2020]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1437,152,402]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FF12F9FBFEA0F87B" bold="true" box="[196,264,1957,1983]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9CC515FF12F9FBFEA9F87B" box="[196,257,1957,1983]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
In Reitter’s collection at 
<collectionCode id="ED6861F8FF9CC515FD92F9FBFD0BF87B" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" box="[580,675,1957,1983]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">HNHM</collectionCode>
, is a pinned female bearing the labels: “Caucasus, Araxesthal, Leder.Reitter” printed, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FE68F995FDF2F820" box="[446,602,1995,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FE68F995FDF2F820" box="[446,602,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23E9854FF9CC515FDB4F994FD0CF820" box="[610,676,1994,2020]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Petri” handwritten, “ 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9CC515FC70F994FB81F820" box="[934,1065,1994,2020]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Holotypus</typeStatus>
, 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9CC515FBE0F994FBDDF820" box="[1078,1141,1994,2020]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1904.0">1904</number>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9CC515FB55F995FACBF820" authority="Petri" authorityName="Petri" box="[1155,1379,1994,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9CC515FB55F995FAB6F820" box="[1155,1310,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus obesus</emphasis>
Petri
</taxonomicName>
” red brimmed museum label, and fitting the description with 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9DC514FC92FEC6FCD0FF76" box="[836,888,152,178]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
locality as Caucasus. It is here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9DC514FF41FEE3FEABFF13" box="[151,259,189,215]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">lectotype</typeStatus>
with “ 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9DC514FE84FEE3FE73FF13" box="[338,475,189,215]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
, Ƥ, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9DC514FDD8FEE3FCCCFF13" authority="Petri., Gultekin" authorityName="Petri., Gultekin" box="[526,868,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9DC514FDD8FEE3FD0FFF12" box="[526,679,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lixus obesus</emphasis>
Petri., Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9DC514FC72FEE3FC4DFF13" box="[932,997,189,215]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2008.0">2008</number>
”. Seven males and four females bear the labels: “Caucasus, Araxesthal, Leder.Reitter”, “ 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9DC514FCC9FEBCFC09FF38" box="[799,929,226,252]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Paratypus</typeStatus>
, 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9DC514FC79FEBCFC58FF38" box="[943,1008,226,252]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1904.0">1904</number>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9DC514FC28FEBCFB40FF38" authority="Petri" authorityName="Petri" box="[1022,1256,226,252]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9DC514FC28FEBCFB08FF3F" box="[1022,1184,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lixus obesus</emphasis>
Petri
</taxonomicName>
” red brimmed museum label, and are all here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9DC514FD05FF56FC2FFEE6" box="[723,903,264,290]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
with “ 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9DC514FC0DFF56FB32FEE6" box="[987,1178,264,290]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Paralectotypus</typeStatus>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9DC514FB71FF56FF56FE83" authority="Petri., Gultekin" authorityName="Petri., Gultekin" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9DC514FB71FF56FAE0FEE5" box="[1191,1352,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lixus obesus</emphasis>
Petri., Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF9DC514FEECFF73FED3FE83" box="[314,379,301,327]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2008.0">2008</number>
”. A male and a female 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF9DC514FD5CFF73FC80FE83" box="[650,808,301,327]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">paralectotype</typeStatus>
were remounted and aedeagus dissected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C363AAB6FF9DC514FF12FF0CFAF1FE56" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC6F93DFF9DC514FF12FF0CFAF1FE56" blockId="17.[151,1437,152,402]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9DC514FF12FF0CFE97FEA8" bold="true" box="[196,319,338,364]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9DC514FDAAFF0CFCA7FEAF" box="[636,783,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypocrita">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9DC514FDAAFF0CFCA7FEAF" box="[636,783,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">L. hypocrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above). In the same museum a female with label “ 
<collectingCountry id="F36EB9ADFF9DC514FF77FF26FE9EFE56" box="[161,310,376,402]" name="Serbia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
, Westliches, Reitter” has been examined. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF9DC514FCBFFF26FC70FE55" box="[873,984,376,401]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF9DC514FCBFFF26FC70FE55" box="[873,984,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">L. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new record for 
<collectingCountry id="F36EB9ADFF9DC514FB14FF26FAFDFE56" box="[1218,1365,376,402]" name="Serbia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
